# Wholesale System Architecture

This diagram represents the high-level system architecture supporting wholesale operations across order intake, system integration, fulfillment, and financial processing.

Retail Partner / Distributor
        │
        │ Purchase Orders
        ▼
Retail Portal / EDI Platform
(NuOrder, JOOR, SPS Commerce, CommerceHub)
        │
        │ Integration
        ▼
ERP System
(NetSuite / SAP / Sage)
        │
        │ Inventory Allocation
        ▼
Warehouse Management System (WMS)
        │
        │ Pick / Pack / Ship
        ▼
Logistics / Carrier Systems
        │
        │ Shipment Confirmation
        ▼
Retail Partner Delivery
        │
        │ Billing
        ▼
Finance / Accounts Receivable

# Wholesale Order Lifecycle

The wholesale order lifecycle represents the operational process from purchase order receipt through invoicing and payment reconciliation.


Purchase Order Received
        │
        ▼
Order QA Validation
(SKU / Pricing / Terms / ATS)
        │
        ▼
Order Entry or EDI Processing
        │
        ▼
Inventory Allocation
        │
        ▼
Release to Warehouse
        │
        ▼
Pick / Pack / Ship
        │
        ▼
Shipment Confirmation (ASN)
        │
        ▼
Invoice Generation
        │
        ▼
Retailer Payment


# EDI Data Pipeline

Electronic Data Interchange (EDI) enables automated communication between retailer systems and internal enterprise systems.

Retailer System
        │
        │ EDI 850
        ▼
EDI Integration Platform
(SPS Commerce / TrueCommerce)
        │
        ▼
ERP Order Creation
        │
        │ Inventory Check
        ▼
Warehouse Fulfillment
        │
        │ EDI 856
        ▼
Shipment Confirmation
        │
        │ EDI 810
        ▼
Invoice Transmission
